  "text": "Title: Integrate SAML SSO with Okta and Azure AD\n\nDescription:\nBusiness Need: Implement enterprise-grade Single Sign-On (SSO) to enhance security and streamline user access. This is crucial for attracting and onboarding enterprise clients who require robust authentication mechanisms.\n\nCurrent Issue: Existing Okta integration has failures that are currently blocking the onboarding of new clients. Resolving this is a high priority.\n\nRequirement: The solution must support integration with both Okta and Azure AD as Identity Providers (IdPs) to cater to a wider range of potential clients.\n\nAcceptance Criteria:\n* Metadata upload endpoint for Service Provider (SP) XML is implemented.\n* Metadata upload endpoint for Identity Provider (IdP) XML is implemented.\n* Certificate rotation is automated every 90 days.\n* Automatic retry mechanism is implemented for 5xx errors with exponential backoff.\n* End-user test flow for both Okta and Azure AD is documented in Confluence.\n\nLabels: security, sso, okta, azure-ad\n\nPriority: High",
